# Empty in std::io - Rust

## Struct [std](../index.html)::[io](index.html)::[Empty](#)

1.0.0 Â· [source](about:blank/src/std/io/util.rs.html#19) Â·

```
#[non_exhaustive]pub struct Empty;
```

Expand description

`Empty` ignores any data written via [`Write`](trait.Write.html "trait std::io::Write"), and will always be empty (returning zero bytes) when read via [`Read`](trait.Read.html "trait std::io::Read").

This struct is generally created by calling [`empty()`](fn.empty.html "fn std::io::empty"). Please see the documentation of [`empty()`](fn.empty.html "fn std::io::empty") for more details.
